task.summary:
interim - refactoring
TODO - figure out metadata management and data/manifests creating workflow.

new model. Atoms are the only entities in the data-space. Compounds and Assets live in the manifest-space only. Compounds store references to atoms or other compounds from their manifests, instead of having a not-clear entity in the data-space for compounds.
I also started defining other components, such as services and data sources.
interim - ManifestFactory, Manifest verification and validation calls + some general refactoring.
interim - added Policy interface and Manifest stream + started implementing some parts of the Atom manifest, URLSource, etc. + added PowerMock to test static methods.

interim - basic model updates.
- custom exceptions - atom, datasource, locations have been simplified and now AtomManifest has references to locations only. - other minor adjustments to the models have been done.
NEXT: - fix tests - complete compound and asset manifests.
removed tests on non-existing interfaces/classes and fixed test in AtomManifestTest
interim - compound and asset manifests have been defined. Most methods still need to be implemented.
interim - basic model: atom manifest done, naive url location done, compound manifest partially done, plus other minor improvements.

interim - basic model - compound and asset manifests are almost finished. Left todo: signatures, managing identitities, generate incarnation GUID for asset, and provide bulletproof verification/validation methods for manifests.
basic model - manifests + started thinking about local impl. of the sea of stuff.
